At this stage in my life, I much prefer wearing glasses (I can=E2=80=99t ha=
ve LASIK surgery), so I need the Zeiss lens inserts; they are easy-to-use, =
but they do make the Vision Pro worse in my experience. First, eye-tracking=
 worked much better without them, and second, bright scenes will induce ref=
lections on the lenses that are very distracting. Moreover, if you stop usi=
ng the lenses and switch to contacts, you have to re-do hand and eye calibr=
ation and re-setup Optic ID =E2=86=A9=EF=B8=8E ( #rf5-12278 )

